OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FLidl offers store finder's 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffee in fight for new       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fcustomers                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Supermarket chain Lidl has said it will
OL,6, pay a finder's fee to anyone who can   
OL,7, find a suitable site for a new store as
OL,8, it targets 1,100 sites by 2025.        
OL,10,FThe fee will be either 1.5% of a       
OL,11,Ffreehold price or 10% of the first     
OL,12,Fyear's rent for leasehold sites.       
OL,14,FFor a #1.5m site purchase, Lidl says   
OL,15,Fthis would equal a fee of #22,500.     
OL,17,FThe UK's sixth largest supermarket,    
OL,18,Fwhich currently has 920 sites, has been
OL,19,Fgrowing rapidly and taking market share
OL,20,Ffrom the big four supermarket chains.  
